%%%
# Hierarchical logistic regression

Per-group random intercepts $a_g$ with a shared mean $\mu_a$ and a
group-level scale $\sigma_a$, plus a single shared slope $b$ on covariate
$x$. For observation $i$ in group $g_i$:

$$\eta_i = a_{g_i} + b\,x_i,\qquad p_i = \operatorname{invlogit}(\eta_i),\qquad y_i \sim \mathrm{Bernoulli}(p_i).$$

Ported from a PyMC model. Placeholder data: $G = 3$ groups, $N = 6$
observations.
%%%

# --- Data (placeholders) ---
G = 3
x_data     = [-1.2, 0.4, 1.1, -0.3, 0.8, 2.0]
group_data = [1, 2, 3, 1, 2, 3]          # group label in 1..G for each obs
y_data     = [0, 1, 1, 0, 1, 1]          # binary outcome for each obs

# --- Priors ---
mu_a ~ Normal(0.0, 1.0)

%%%
Group-intercept scale. PyMC specified Gamma by MEAN/SD (mu=2, sigma=1);
FlatPPL's Gamma is shape/rate, so convert: shape = mu^2/sigma^2 = 4,
rate = mu/sigma^2 = 2.
%%%
sigma_a ~ Gamma(shape = 4.0, rate = 2.0)

% Per-group intercepts: G iid draws sharing mean mu_a and scale sigma_a.
a ~ iid(Normal(mu_a, sigma_a), G)

% Heavy-tailed slope prior: location-scale Student-t, nu=3, mu=0, sigma=2.5.
b ~ locscale(StudentT(3.0), 0.0, 2.5)

prior = lawof(record(mu_a = mu_a, sigma_a = sigma_a, a = a, b = b))

# --- Linear predictor and likelihood ---
%%%
a[group_data] gathers each observation's group intercept (array-of-indices
subset selection); broadcast the affine map and the link over observations.
%%%
eta = a[group_data] .+ b .* x_data
p   = invlogit.(eta)

y ~ Bernoulli.(p)

# --- Posterior assembly ---
forward_kernel = kernelof(record(y = y), mu_a = mu_a, sigma_a = sigma_a, a = a, b = b)
L              = likelihoodof(forward_kernel, record(y = y_data))
posterior      = bayesupdate(L, prior)
